The paper is primarily focused on developing a distributed spreadsheet for browsing very large datasets, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). However, the paper also introduces visualization sketches as a key technique for producing compact data visualizations, which involves computer graphics principles and human-computer interaction (cs.HC, cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses parallelization and computation techniques for scaling the spreadsheet, which falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS).
